==English==

===Etymology===
From late Latin [[pragmaticus]], from Greek [[πραγματικός]], from '''[[πράγμα]]''' ‘[[pragma]], thing’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/prægˈmætɪk/}}
*{{audio|en-us-pragmatic.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

#[[Practical]], concerned with making [[decision]]s and [[action]]s that are [[useful]] in [[practice]], [[not]] just [[theory]]
#:''The sturdy furniture in the student lounge was '''pragmatic''', but unattractive.''

====Synonyms====
*(''practical''): [[down-to-earth]], [[functional]], [[practical]], [[utilitarian]]

